<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-218-231 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 377 207</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 21 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for PC: DR offers UKP 59 upgrade to DR-DOS. (Digital ResearchInc., United Kingdom pound, DR-DOS 5.0 operating system) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Research Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   DR DOS 5.0 (Operating system) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionUpgrading.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR PC: DR Offers UKP 59 Upgrade To DR-DOS 5.0 02/21/91 NEWBURY,BERKSHIRE, ENGLAND, 1991 FEB 21 (NB) -- Digital Research has announced it isoffering all existing users of DOS packages the chance to upgrade to DR-DOS5.0 for UKP 59.andM;According to Richard Gibbs, DR DOS' international product marketing manager,the package is the only DOS operating system that can currently maximize thepower of PCs and applications.andM;&quot;As well as routinely freeing 620K of RAM for applications, MIS managementupgrading to DR DOS 5.0 could overcome many of the standardization problemsassociated with multiple versions of MS- DOS,&quot; he said.andM;Gibbs went on to say that, since companies have different versions of DOSinstalled on their PCs, considerable staff resources are wasted on trainingto use specific versions of the operating system.andM;&quot;By upgrading to DR DOS 5.0, these companies can establish a consistent DOSstandard across all hardware platforms, while raising the overall performanceof their DOS based operations,&quot; he said.andM;(Steve Gold/19910221/Press andamp; Public Contact: Digital Research - Tel:0635-35304)</TEXT></DOC>